  "overnight": false,
  "slug": "galette-dough",
  "source": "This recipe is based on Athena Calderone’s “Cook Beautiful” book.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "In a food processor, pulse <Ingredient name=\"all-purpose flour\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"coconut sugar\"  />, and <Ingredient name=\"salt\"  />, until combined. You should work fast with this recipe, and never let the butter melt. It’s a good idea to keep the dough in the fridge between the steps.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Cut the butter into 2 cm cubes, and add it to the flour mixture. Pulse until the butter is mixed with the flour but not fully incorporated into it.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Pour slowly <Ingredient name=\"buttermilk\"  /> or yogurt into the dough mixture, pulsing until all the buttermilk is absorbed. The dough should look dry and crumbly at this stage, with visible pieces of cold butter.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Take a container about 15x20 cm, transfer the dough into the container, and gently press to incorporate loose bits. Cover the container, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.",
          "pause": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
